I guess the `otLinkedBuffer` is allocated from the `TCP receive buffer`.

Can ALP locate a `otLinkedBuffer` itself and receive data to it (TCP set it to reference the data in `receive buffer` ) ?

```c++
otLinkedBuffer recvBuffer;

otTcpActiveReceiveByReference(aInstance, aSocket, &recvBuffer);

// Now data is referenced by recvBuffer.mData and recvBuffer.mLength
```

I am not sure if this can free TCP from having to allocating `otLinkedBuffer` from `receive buffer`. Thoughts?

