Not for this PR but, This appears to be a class-level value (i.e. it is constant across all instances of this class since it only differs on the `field_modulus` property.).

If that is the case, then it *should* be possible to populate this at the class level either by doing it manually *or* by doing it using a metaclass.  Rough untested code looks something like:


```python
class FQPMetaclass(type):
    def __new__(cls, name, bases, attrs):
        field_modulus = attrs.get('field_modulus', cls.field_modulus)
        if field_modulus is not None:
            attrs['FQP_corresponding_FQ_class'] = type("FQP_corresponding_FQ_class", (FQ,), {'field_modulus": field_modulus})
        return super().__new__(name, bases, attrs)
```

