I used [dataclasses](https://docs.python.org/3/library/dataclasses.html) in ConnectionPool code. They were introduced in Python 3.7. It would be possible to write the same code without dataclasses, but it would be less convenient, and since
* Python 3.6 [ended its life in 2021](https://docs.python.org/3/library/dataclasses.html);
* it affects only ConnectionPool and all other old features are available for Python 3.x;
we decided to support only 3.7 here.

By the way, the main reason for dropping Python 2 was our implementation of connection interface (we use metaclasses).

