@arcanefoam Since the only purpose of the `continue` is to prevent calling `return`, you can just invert the logic.  Instead of

    for vals in ((v, other[k]) for k, v in self.items()):
        if vals[0] == vals[1]:
            continue
        return method(vals[0], vals[1])

Do
            
    for vals in ((v, other[k]) for k, v in self.items()):
        if vals[0] != vals[1]:
            return method(vals[0], vals[1])

